<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2716] [iPOJO] Failure when creating proxies for classes in java.* packages</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2716</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears that iPOJO is no longer able to proxy classes in java.* packages. This used to work, but it seems recent JVM changes no longer allow it. To see an example, refer to the iPOJO example in ch 12 in the OSGi in Action companion code (&lt;a href=&quot;http://code.google.com/p/osgi-in-action/downloads/list&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://code.google.com/p/osgi-in-action/downloads/list&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12491910">FELIX-2716</key>
            <summary>[iPOJO] Failure when creating proxies for classes in java.* packages</summary>
